1
00:00:00,320 --> 00:00:17,840
All right, Crawley here again for our final chapter. A basic hospital plan gives valuable help for an average illness, but the specific purpose of a Major Medical Expense policy is to rescue people from the extremely serious financial effects of a medical catastrophe.

2
00:00:17,840 --> 00:00:29,760
It is not meant to take over every single penny of a disaster. It is built entirely on cost-sharing through two mechanisms: a deductible and coinsurance.

3
00:00:29,760 --> 00:00:45,600
First, the insured must pay the initial expenses up to a given amount, the deductible. Just as soon as that deductible is accumulated, the policy takes over and pays 75% or 80% of further covered expenses subject to a maximum limit.

4
00:00:45,600 --> 00:00:54,879
Clients always ask, why not eliminate the deductible so the policy pays everything? From a practical standpoint, offering a policy that broad would be impossibly expensive.

5
00:00:54,879 --> 00:01:03,440
Cost-sharing keeps premiums affordable and establishes a restraint on extravagant medical charges, giving the insured a financial reason to hold expenses down.

6
00:01:03,440 --> 00:01:16,640
Of course, health insurance has rigid exclusions. Standard individual plans will not cover sickness or injury existing prior to the coverage, nervous or mental diseases, or normal pregnancy and childbirth.

7
00:01:16,640 --> 00:01:26,640
They also strictly exclude injuries covered by workman's compensation laws, acts of war, injuries sustained while serving in the armed forces, or injuries from operating military or experimental aircraft.

8
00:01:26,640 --> 00:01:37,840
Health insurance isn't just about paying bills. It's about keeping families intact when their bodies betray them. Master these definitions, know the exclusions, and protect your clients.